{{template "base/head" .}}
<div role="main" aria-label="{{if .IsSigned}}{{ctx.Locale.Tr "dashboard"}}{{else}}{{ctx.Locale.Tr "home_title"}}{{end}}" class="page-content home">
	<div class="tw-mb-8 tw-px-8">
		<div class="center">
			<img class="logo" width="220" height="220" src="{{AssetUrlPrefix}}/img/logo.svg" alt="{{ctx.Locale.Tr "logo"}}">
			<div class="hero">
				<h1 class="ui icon header title tw-text-balance">
					ProcessGit
					<div class="sub header">
						ProcessGit is Git for executable processes.
						Version, review, and release workflows as portable algorithms — so teams and AI agents execute the same “single source of truth”, every time.
					</div>
				</h1>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="ui stackable middle very relaxed page grid">
		<div class="eight wide center column">
			<h1 class="hero ui icon header">
				What is a Processpository?
			</h1>
			<p class="large tw-text-balance">
				A Processpository is a Git repository that stores executable process algorithms.
				Instead of burying process knowledge in documents and tribal memory, you store the real operational logic as versioned artifacts: models, decision rules, test scenarios, and release tags.
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class="eight wide center column">
			<h1 class="hero ui icon header">
				Why this matters
			</h1>
			<p class="large tw-text-balance">
				Traditional process documentation drifts. People interpret. Tools diverge. AI agents hallucinate.
				ProcessGit restores the old discipline: a single canonical definition, peer-reviewed and traceable — with history, diffs, approvals, and releases.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="ui stackable middle very relaxed page grid">
		<div class="sixteen wide center column">
			<h1 class="hero ui icon header">
				Built for UAPF packages
			</h1>
			<p class="large tw-text-balance">
				Import UAPF (.uapf) packages to keep workflows, decisions, and governance metadata bundled as one portable artifact — validated on entry and stored in Git as the authoritative SSOT.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
{{template "base/footer" .}}
